<!--   BL II   -->
<eventList name="BP_BURST_LASER_II_REWARD_BAD">
	<event>
		<text>The strange one-eyed humanoid who spent a few hours hunched over with his tools brings your new weapon in an old crate. It looks... Wrong. This didn't work out so well, but you have to pay.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_SUBSTANDARD"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>They get the blueprint set-up and start working. Their tools are unregulated and outdated, though, and they end up having to do many power inneficient work-arounds.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_FAULTY"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The building process is behind closed doors. After a while, you notice a smell of something burnt. This doesn't look good.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_MALFUNCTIONING"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>	
	<event>
		<text>The alien building your weapon is visibly shaking, probably collateral effect from drugs. He does the job, but nothing is quite well attached.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_UNRELIABLE"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The elderly human builder takes the blueprint from your hand, glances at it and exclaims "Bah! These new schematics are terrible. I'll build it the old fashioned way." Before you can stop him he throws the blueprint away.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_OUTDATED"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The doors close and you don't get a chance to watch the building process. After a few hours, a Rock Man with delivery uniform brings a crate to your ship, it's your new weapon. You deposit the money in the workshop's account.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-52" max="-48"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
</eventList>

<eventList name="BP_BURST_LASER_II_REWARD_REG">
	<event>
		<text>A computer takes your blueprint and aids the chief-mechanic in the construction process. After some hours, you get your weapon.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>A young engineer supervises the work. She seems really glad to get to work on a bigger project for once. After some time, you get your new weapon.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The doors close and you don't get a chance to watch the building process. After a few hours, a Rock Man with a delivery uniform brings a crate to your ship, it's your new weapon. You transfer over the scrap.</text>		
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The blueprint is taken inside and the building process starts. The worker team has people from many species, and they tick together like clockwork. The weapon is built better than the required specifications.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_VOLATILE"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Some of the engineers are system overheating enthusiasts. They add custom-built heatsinks to the project, allowing for higher-temperature blasts.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_INCENDIARY"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The team is supervised by a master weapons builder. He's been in the trade for a very long time, and knows intricacies that even the weapon's original designers wouldn't notice. The work is very well done.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_QUALITY"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>An "Advanced Power Generation Technology" student requests to aid in the job, so that he can use the data for his End-of-Term project. He offers to pay for some of the job too. (Cost reduced by 5 scrap)</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-62" max="-58"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_UPGRADED"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>	
	<event>
		<text>A Zoltan is project leader, and he notices the schematics are outdated on what the current rules-of-engagement laws permit. The energy being calibrates the weapon to have a more coherent blast, avoiding damage to living beings. At least it's cheaper (Cost reduced by 5 scrap)</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-62" max="-58"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_SAFE"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Some of the Rock mechanics working on the project know a trick that speeds up the shots and avoid loss of coherence when hitting the target, causing a penetrating blow.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-67" max="-63"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_PENETRATING"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
</eventList>

<eventList name="BP_BURST_LASER_II_REWARD_GOOD">
	<event>
		<text>The entire process is automated, and your weapon is built with top-of-the line parts. Surely worth the price!</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-78" max="-82"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_QUALITY"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The chief engineer seems interested in your project, and decides to tone down on the automation to work on it himself, with the help of a few of his students. It's nearly perfect.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-78" max="-82"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_CUSTOM"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<!--<event>
		<text>The assembly line's computer has incredible energy routing schematics, and your weapon is built to great power efficiency standards.</text>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-42" max="-38"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_OPTIMIZED"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>-->
	<event>
		<text>The engineers have used some new, experimental capacitors that charge way faster, allowing the weapon to charge up more quickly.</text>
		<remove name="BPW_BURST_LASER_II"/>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-78" max="-82"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_UPGRADED"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>An elderly Engi (do Engi age?) decides your project deserves his special attention. He is an old master, and coordinates the project focusing on a quicker charging weapon.</text>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-78" max="-82"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_ADVANCED"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>A Mantis engineer! And you thought you had seen everything. He changes the energy pattern from the default one on the blueprint, making the blasts more damaging to the targets hull.</text>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="scrap" min="-78" max="-82"/>
		</item_modify>
		<weapon name="LASER_BURST_3_HULL_RIPPER"/>
		<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
	</event>
</event>
<!-- end BL II -->

